									<td bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td class="subjectbar"  style="font-size: 10pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
									Discussion about upcoming changes to Bard PBAE songs.
																	</td>
							<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">		
		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 
		id="individual_options_1786_table" 
		onClick="setId('1786');show(this,'individual_options_1786','right',false);" 
		onDblClick="setId('1786');show(this,'individual_options_1786','right',false);" 
	 >
	<tr class=clickable>
					<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
		<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='' width=11 height=28></td>
		<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
	</table>
	
	
</td></tr>
						
		<tr>
			
			<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>

						
							
				
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=3262' class="auth_text" style="font-weight:bold;"><span style='color:#33CC00;font-weight:bold; '>Grumbuk-Dev</span></a>
				<br>

								
				<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
									EQ Programmer
								<br>
									Posts: 115<br>
													Registered: 03-04-2004
				
				</span>
									<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=3262'>			
	
		</a><br>

				<span class=text_smallest>
								Server: Test<br>
								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 427 times<br>
									</span>

												</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify;  background-color: #000016;   background-image: none;  background-repeat: repeat-x; " >
												Feedback is good. This threads on the various forums are getting big, but I'll try to address what I can. I've started this thread in order to try to keep track of at least my involvment in this topic.<br><br>Personally, I'm hoping to see a different solution than the one currently on test because I'm not sure that particular fix is truly able to prevent PBAE kiting in the first place. It seemed like it would, but as someone else noticed there might be a way to play with the timing to do it anyways. Even so, I expect the current code on test will probably go to live servers because we're already locking things down for the Omens release to try to make sure things are as stable as possible. Nothing says we can't change it later if & when we decide there is an alternative that is healthier for the game however, and this is where the feedback comes in. We just want to solve what we consider to be a problem with the game.<br><br><br>So let me go down the various threads I'm aware of and try to categorize main points people have made.<br><br>---------------<br><br>* First and foremost, why did this even come up when there are the top 10 issues lists? This is a very appropriate question. For a long time now we have been aware of PBAE being a problem we wanted to have fixed, but we hadn't yet thought of a good way to do it. Over time, conversations occurred about this and many other game balance topics, and we realized what be a good solution to this specific problem that wouldn't be too hard to implement. It's not like we scheduled a meeting on this - the topic has come up over and over again for a long time now with no solutions presenting themselves until recently. The fix was all code based, and a programmer had some free time one afternoon and was asked to implement the change. Most of the top 10 issues are more design issues than code issues, and as such require the design team to work on them. Sometimes we realize we can fix a problem with a few lines of code in just the right place though, and this is one of those things.<br><br>--<br><br>* This change is specific to the PBAE songs that bards can memorize and cast with a gem, and should not be affecting anything else.<br><br>--<br><br>* The 10 mob limit suggestions - The HoH fix involved a fairly time consuming script addition to the NPCs in the zone and I don't expect anyone to choose to do that over a global fix.<br><br>--<br><br>* Adding special NPCs or modifying NPCs to make PBAE kiting difficult/impossible. The notion of adding zone specific NPCs to complicate bard kiting is something I don't believe the design guys will want to do (mostly due to time constraints and the fact a code solution is probably as good or better). On the same note, any changes that would require design team to modify the inventory or spell capability is of NPCs in general is unlikely to happen due to the sheer number of NPCs in the game that would need to be edited. Moreover, this has the risk of affecting other classes. We'd like this fix to be as targeted on the problem as possible with a minimum of side effects. Also, adding NPCs to all the zones isn't a practical one for us due to the time involved. This particular idea, while it may sound simple, is quite a hassle for the designers. All these issues point us in the direction of modifying the specific spell behaviors directly since it is a global solution.<br><br>--<br><br>If I overheard the conversations correctly, I believe Rytan did some calculations about the DPS potential of a bard using PBAE it was a pretty amazing and substantial amount of DPS that a bard can produce. I will try to get Rytan to give me the specifics on this but I'm sure someone could do that math before I talk him into stepping aside from the crunch time tasks he's in right now. Basically, the DPS that these songs can produce far exceeds every other class's DPS ability by a *lot*. It's out of whack and has to be fixed.<br><br>--<br><br>* As I said originally, this does not include all PBAE songs. It only includes ones that do damage. Yes this does mean most of the PBAE songs. "Most" is not the same as "All". <br><br>--<br><br>* The server side lag due to PBAE kiting *is* substantial and *does* affect other players. I happen to be the exact person who knows exactly what I'm talking about here because I am the person who 1) helped write the new pathing system, and 2) wrote the new collision system, and 3) have spent literally weeks running server profiling tools testing server loads and identifying what causes server lag. It just so happens that running a bunch of NPCs around in a circle is bad for CPU server loads, and does affect everyone else that happens to be on the same hardware. This is server lag, not video lag. The server doesn't care how many corpses are sitting around stationary. But when the server is asked to run path finder code on dozens of NPCs as they do full collision math as they run over the zone geometry, the server slows down and everyone in the zone & other zones on the box is affected. As a player you generally only notice tell lag or NPC warping, but it does affect gameplay in many ways. Minimizing server lag is an ongoing task for me and the other programmers, and when stuff like this hits the radar as being a problem it's a priority for us to fix it.<br><br>--<br><br>* It does seem reasonable to have the 54 slow scale up to the 62 MoM if this change stays in place. I'll forward this suggestion.<br><br>--<br><br>* Leaving the range of the song intact while nerfing the damage component is unfortunatly a lot more complicated than it sounds. The damage is a dot, which means it's a buff, and spells only leave one buff on a target. Not having the dot component means anything else that was on the buff would have to go away also. We'd have to make some fairly deep changes to the spell system to support this kind of change. <br><br>--<br><br>* The extended notes related comments are pretty much off topic - that AA was always intended only to work with beneficial spells. <br><br>-- <br><br>* Making mob movement more random, or doing other similar changes to the movement code is a possible alternative to this change. But not really likely due to the complexity of the pathing system in general. It's a possibility though.<br><br>--<br><br>* The fact is, bards can solo just fine without PBAE kiting. Personally, I'd like to see all classes have the ability to solo at some productive level that generates slightly less experience than grouping - but that's just my opinion. I think being able to solo is an important part of the game because not everyone can commit the time to a group every time they want to log in for a random amount of time. This change has nothing to do with any other classes ability (or lack of ability) to solo. <br><br>--<br><br>* Call it a nerf if you want, but being able to kill 30+ NPCs at a time is flat out broken and is going to be fixed. It is plainly obvious that this is unhealthy for the game, and we are going to fix it. <br><br>--<br><br><br><br>------------<br><br><br>Keep in mind I'm just a programmer here, and I don't speak for the design team, but I'm trying to help make sure that the solution to the problem we have decided to fix is the best of the available options. I'd rather just see the system behave in a way that is fun and not exploitable. <br><br>My current favorite solution to this problem is to add a new component to the PBAE line that would give the NPC a random chance to have the ability to summon the person who landed the DOT on it that granted this ability (ie the bard). Seems like if we did this, the spells could be left largely intact and it would stop PBAE from being the problem it is. And bards wouldn't ever have a reason to stand still (I don't like that part either)<br><br>If you have other suggestions that are different from the ones proposed above, please let me know. I'll try my best to keep up with this thread and to forward useful comments to the right people.
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>Eric Cosky - "Grumbuk"<br>Assistant Lead Programmer, EverQuest<br>Sony Online Entertainment
							</div>
																
