												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>Grumbuk-Dev wrote:<BR>Personally, I'm hoping to see a different solution than the one currently on test because I'm not sure that particular fix is truly able to prevent PBAE kiting in the first place. It seemed like it would, <STRONG>but as someone else noticed there might be a way to play with the timing to do it anyways</STRONG>.
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I posted the following&nbsp;on EQ Diva NOT to start a fleet of macroquest Stutterstep AE DoT&nbsp;Bards, but to show that the hard-core AE kiting bard population can and most likely will&nbsp;continue to hard-core exp and PL. In short, the new "fix" will only hurt the casual players and raiders, while do little then add a few hours macro reworking for the professional PL's and EXpers. By professional I refer to those that use macros to create level 1-65 toons in a few days time, or the guild PLers to create an army of hydra, or those people that sell PLing for real life cash.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<DIV><SPAN>Obvious work around to the stand still problem for the macro AE kiters: Create a macro that <BR><BR>1) runs and turns a distance three seconds ahead of the train <BR>2) stop moving <BR>3) begin casting AE song <BR>4) when song is casted and mobs are DoTed repeat to step #1 <BR><BR>You will still be able to kill an unlimited number of mobs. However it will take roughly twice as long and require a wider kite radius. <BR><BR>With the stand and cast nurf the professional PLers/EXPers using macroquest or similar programs will get exp, yes twice as slow but still nice exp while you sleep/work/shop/watch tv. The casual player will simply get nurfed. The raid bard on AE pulls will get nurfed sometimes. The tradeskill farmer will get nurfed (unless he is running a farm macro!). <BR><BR>I once made an AE DoT macro, made it work well, then never used it again. I got less then 1 of my AA by AE kiting, the majority of my 403AA were from groups. <BR><BR><BR>Grumbuk, you might reduce server load by reducing the number of bards AE kiting. But the bards with 700+ AA will find a way as they always do. <BR><BR>Please leave it alone, all of it. You are only forcing 1% of EQs population into using macro programs to AE kite, while pissing off the other 99% of EQ's population who will loose some of their utility on raids (and the high Risk vs Reward soloers). <BR><BR><BR>/sigh</SPAN></DIV>
																		
