			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Hi Grumbuk,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I understand exactly where you are comming from on the development perspective. Frankly I am shocked the code isn't locked down already for a sept 14th release, but that is beside the point.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Have you thought about making a small change to the range nerf calculation? Instead of checking if the bard is moving, can you instead check to see if they are on 10 or more hate lists? If so reduce the range if they are moving.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It is a small change but it would let us use AE's in group encounters, and some of the smaller raid AE encounters. I don't like the thought of any nerf that impacts an incredibly large portion of a classes abilities, but it is much better than the current solution on test that effectively eliminates an entire section of the song book (bards have to keep moving, it is the nature of the class. We end up meleeing and we have to follow mobs, keep tanks in range of songs etc).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
