			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												Thank you for the detailed explanation of the situation from the other side. I appreciate the post, & the obvious desire for our input on our AE DoTs & kiting. I would, however, appreciate it if we could avoid describing this usage as 'exploiting'. Bards were given AE DoTs. Bards were given the ability to move while casting. If 1+1=2 is an exploit, then by all means please nerf math. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><br>That said, I can understand & accept the desire to change the functionality of bard AE DoTs after reading the dev-side view. Knowing now that a 10-mob limit would be much harder to implement, I have to second the suggestion of simply reducing the DoT damage component. This seems to be simply a code-based change & would probably be even easier to implement than the 'moving range = x, non-moving range = y' thing since it only involves changing the numbers in an already existing field. This would directly lower the DPS, reducing the viability of our AE DoTs as kiting tools while still letting us reposition during AE groups. We'd still bring some usefulness to such groups with AE slow, manasong (yes, it IS playing! ;p ), & some minor DoT damage (not like our DoT damage was a major contribution to such groups anyway, as letting multiple mobs live long enough for DoTs to do much damage is rather counterproductive to survival).<br><br>Your suggestion that our AE DoTs have a random 'mob summoning ability' component to the buff they land on mobs is creative & fun. It seems like that would be harder coding than just lowering the damage, but if you guys are game for it, it sounds good to me.<br><br>Thanks again for the dialogue. Please do reconsider whatever changes are pushed now after OoW is out.
																		
										</td></tr>
