</td></tr>
						
		<tr>
			
			<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>

						
							
				
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=12741' class="auth_text" style="font-weight:bold;"><span style='color:#336600;'>Klapton</span></a>
				<br>

								
				<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
									Journeyman
								<br>
									Posts: 58<br>
													Registered: 03-24-2004
				
				</span>
									<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=12741'>			
	
		</a><br>

				<span class=text_smallest>
								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 243 times<br>
									</span>

									
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P><FONT color=#66ccff>First off, thank you very much for listening.&nbsp; I have been one of the most vocal whiners since this came down.&nbsp; Please understand that my intention was to be an extremely "squeaky wheel" in hopes that we would be listened to.&nbsp; Again, THANK YOU.&nbsp; Your post was extrememly informative.&nbsp; I was most facinated by your explanation of how AE kiting affects CPU time on the server.&nbsp; hehe</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#66ccff>I would like to respond to a few of the items you posted.</FONT><BR></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>Grumbuk-Dev wrote:<BR><BR>---------------<BR><BR><STRONG>* First and foremost, why did this even come up when there are the top 10 issues lists? This is a very appropriate question.</STRONG> --</P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><FONT color=#66ccff>This was my main complaint.&nbsp; Thank you for acknowleging it.</FONT></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>If I overheard the conversations correctly, I believe <STRONG>Rytan did some calculations about the DPS potential of a bard using PBAE it was a pretty amazing and substantial amount of DPS that a bard can produce.</STRONG> I will try to get Rytan to give me the specifics on this but I'm sure someone could do that math before I talk him into stepping aside from the crunch time tasks he's in right now. Basically, the DPS that these songs can produce far exceeds every other class's DPS ability by a *lot*. It's out of whack and has to be fixed.</P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><FONT color=#00ccff>Bard AE dps is only amazing if there are LOTS of mobs to hit.&nbsp; (The math is easy... multiply song dps * number of mobs).&nbsp; I wonder though, if Rytan's calculations include the time needed to PULL a train like that?&nbsp; Often, it takes just as long to GATHER all those mobs as it takes to kill them.</FONT></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>* The server side lag due to PBAE kiting *is* substantial and *does* affect other players. I happen to be the exact person who knows exactly what I'm talking about here because I am the person who 1) helped write the new pathing system, and 2) wrote the new collision system, and 3) have spent literally weeks running server profiling tools testing server loads and identifying what causes server lag. It just so happens that running a bunch of NPCs around in a circle is bad for CPU server loads, and does affect everyone else that happens to be on the same hardware. This is server lag, not video lag. The server doesn't care how many corpses are sitting around stationary. But when the server is asked to run path finder code on dozens of NPCs as they do full collision math as they run over the zone geometry, the server slows down and everyone in the zone &amp; other zones on the box is affected. As a player you generally only notice tell lag or NPC warping, but it does affect gameplay in many ways. Minimizing server lag is an ongoing task for me and the other programmers, and when stuff like this hits the radar as being a problem it's a priority for us to fix it.<BR></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>Again, very interesting indeed.&nbsp; Not only does it "hog mobs" and zone disruption (especially when a bard messes it up and trains to zone instead of taking their death like a man), but it messes up the whole server!</FONT>
<HR>
</P>
<P><STRONG>* It does seem reasonable to have the 54 slow scale up to the 62 MoM if this change stays in place. I'll forward this suggestion.<BR></STRONG><BR></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff><STRONG>THIS ONE WOULD MAKE GROUPING AND RAIDING BARDS VERY HAPPY!!!</STRONG>&nbsp; I used Melody of Mischief on single pulls all the time until I got Requiem of Time, because it was the best slow I had.&nbsp; (Had to keep 51 snare loaded for multiples).&nbsp; As long as it is indeed only song that do DAMAGE, not all DETRIMENTAL songs, then this should work.&nbsp; So, a pre-RoT Bard still has a decent Slow (54 AE slow) and AE groups and raids can still have some nice AE damage mitigation that makes those encounters work.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>This would also mean that I can still use lvl 20 AE slow while I GATHER my greenies for slaughter then stand still while I AE em to death when farming tradeskill junk etc.&nbsp; (Mass slaughtering green cons for tradeskill drops and/or faction is one of the nicest uses of our AE damage songs, imo, and does not affect game balance).</FONT></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><BR>* Making mob movement more random, or doing other similar changes to the movement code is a possible alternative to this change. But not really likely due to the complexity of the pathing system in general. It's a possibility though.<BR></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>Simply changing the runspeed of mobs within the same zone would stop many.&nbsp; In Dulak, for example, do NOT get those rats in your kite, hehe.&nbsp; They run faster than the other mobs, and will nibble away at you the whole time, and if the stun you, it's all over.&nbsp; Fortunately for the kiting bard, they are indifferent.&nbsp; If about one third of the mobs (or pick one mob type in the zone that pops all over) had SoW speed, AE kiting would be REAL hard.</FONT></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>* Call it a nerf if you want, but being able to kill 30+ NPCs at a time is flat out broken and is going to be fixed. It is plainly obvious that this is unhealthy for the game, and we are going to fix it. <BR><BR></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><FONT color=#66ccff>I guess if the fact that 30 mobs are engaged at once, and die at close to the same time is out of balance... but there ARE classes that can solo the same 30 mobs JUST as fast as the Bard, and the risk to those other players is FAR less.&nbsp; (One mistake by the bard during the 20 minutes or more it takes for those mobs to die, and the bard is dead).&nbsp; I'm NOT asking for those other classes to be nerfed, mind you.&nbsp; But AE kiting is NOT a fast killing method.&nbsp; One reason I don't do it is because it is mind-numbingly tedious and slow.&nbsp; Well, so is Chant Kiting for that matter.&nbsp; /shrug</FONT>
<HR>
</P>
<P>Keep in mind I'm just a programmer here, and I don't speak for the design team, but I'm trying to help make sure that the solution to the problem we have decided to fix is the best of the available options. I'd rather just see the system behave in a way that is fun and not exploitable. <BR><BR><STRONG>My current favorite solution to this problem is to add a new component to the PBAE line that would give the NPC a random chance to have the ability to summon the person who landed the DOT on it that granted this ability (ie the bard).</STRONG> Seems like if we did this, the spells could be left largely intact and it would stop PBAE from being the problem it is. And bards wouldn't ever have a reason to stand still (I don't like that part either)</P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>Pretty cool idea.&nbsp; Kinda like my "Summoning Prankster" mob idea, but clearly easier to implement.</FONT></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>If you have other suggestions that are different from the ones proposed above, please let me know. I'll try my best to keep up with this thread and to forward useful comments to the right people.<BR></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>Some at eqdiva have suggested an idea.&nbsp; It is the opinion of many, that AE kiting at lvl 65 is INDEED one of the only decent solo xp methods for bards.&nbsp; Chant Kiting takes WAY too long.&nbsp; Swarm Kiting, because of the Charm caps, is only viable by hogging lower level content, gathering large numbers of mobs (just like AE kiting-- only the Bard's aggro is WAY less, making it FAR more dangerous for passers-by).&nbsp; With this change, many lvl 65 AE kiters WILL go back to swarming tier 1 and 2 PoP content, and you will have similar problems.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>They argue that AE kiting at lvl 65 is NOT out of balance with other solo classes.&nbsp; (Yes, I am making a difference here.&nbsp; People often choose a class because solo play is viable, and we know this as a reality in the game.&nbsp; You could, in the interest of "fairness" nerf all soloing to match that of a Warrior...)&nbsp; There are other classes that can grind 2 or 3 AAs per hour.&nbsp; A skilled 65 Bard AE kiting can get about 2 an hour, if they get the right mobs, and the right spot uncamped.&nbsp; This is not unreasonable.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>Their suggestion is an AA with required lvl 65 that would activate the damage portion of their AE songs, and/or un-nerf the range while moving thing.&nbsp; Basically, only lvl 65 Bards would be able to do it then.&nbsp; (You would not have people rolling bards, AEing their way to 65 in two weeks, then having no clue how to pull or cc for groups etc.)</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>Again, thank you for interacting with the Bard community.&nbsp; I apologize (kinda, hehe) for the level of stink I have helped to raise on the issue.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>Klapton, Moderator, Eqdiva</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#6699ff>Scherzo Glissando, Maestro, Molto Espressivo, Firiona Vie</FONT></P>
<P><BR></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
