												<DIV>Again, back to the macro problem. Do normal people AE kite by hand for long durations of time? (This includes using autocircle.) I suspect it is not the normal person who does an AE kite by hand&nbsp;for short&nbsp;peroids of times. I believe its the endless hours of AE kiting by macro that makes up the majority of AE kite hours. And as I pointed out in an earlier post there is a simple work around with the macros that will only take a few hours to write and post. Then the AE kiting will continue as normal with not much gained (server lag reduction) and a lot lost (angry bards who do not AE kite but will loose some utility and flexability in group and raid.)</DIV>
