			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>SlowmotionSZ,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Nice try, but the places it is a problem are exactly NOT the PoP zones, it is more the LoY and old world zones it is a problem in. It isn't the 65 folks that are causing this problem in PoP kiting for their personal gain, it's the PLers of themsleves and others that is in the lower zones.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But the point is moot, PBAE kiting is dead, at every level.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;Grumbak wrote:* The fact is, bards can solo just fine without PBAE kiting. Personally, I'd like to see all classes have the ability to solo at some productive level that generates slightly less experience than grouping - but that's just my opinion. I think being able to solo is an important part of the game because not everyone can commit the time to a group every time they want to log in for a random amount of time. This change has nothing to do with any other classes ability (or lack of ability) to solo. <BR>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's over sportsfans, thats what I am reading from this. My guess is, the servers will be taxed to the limit with the new expansion, and anything&nbsp;like AE kiting will put too much of a burden on them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There are several other fixes I can think of that would allow it to be limited, but really, until I hear different, I am assuming they want the ability destroyed completely, 3 mobs or 50, for Bards. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If I am wrong on this, and SoE has no problem with limited kites (which I do not believe) then please say so. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Assuming I am not wrong, I will more than likely be hanging up the drum, I am&nbsp;disgusted of a nerf on top of a nerf on top of a nerf,&nbsp;but heres a fix for those who don't, to use AE for other reasons:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Add a self snare component, allowing movement, but greatly decreased, unresistable, lasting 3 ticks, as the song lands. 35% or so should screw the pooch, while allowing positioning easily enough for AE groups and raids and such. Shouldn't be a problem to code I would think. You could even make each ae song have different levels of snare, and all overwrite each other. Welcome to ae kiting uselessness. It will be so unprofitable to AE, taking so long, assuming you find that one song that allows you to work with the snare, on one particular mob.. A better idea, add the POSSIBILTY of a snare.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I really would like to hear I am wrong on this Grumbak, although I suspect I won't, and your silence on this will be answer enough.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If I am told different, 10 mob or any number you care to put a limit on can also be fixed by simply doing this fix, and giving us a straight AE DD song, with a cap of 10 mobs. If the server can handle 10, then make it a 30 range, and allow it to be chain sung.</DIV>
<DIV>The mobs running in circles dont add to the server load issue nearly as much as the damage and such I would assume? It also makes bards want to pull smaller, as more mobs is a better chance to die on a stun. Why pull what you cannot kill? Bards also have an issue with lag on this, it's what kills us most often. Make the song level 65. basically an AE scream. Not to mention, a hella fun song<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
																		
