			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												Ok if we really want to end aoe kiting we need to let go of the variable running speeds idea.  I frequently kited mobs with all types of running speed in the very same kite with no problem whatsoever.  The only time that would remotely cause a problem is if the a mob was fast enough to hit you hit running, and even then that is manageable by eliminating that mob or mobs from your kite, hello fade, hello mez, hello highsun, hello etc etc etc.<br><br>It seems the amount of work is a big factor in what you guys WILL do fix this problem.  No surprise there after playing this game for 4 years.  Instead of eliminating all damage on the detrimental songs which would seem like more work vs. lowering the overall damage(BASE DAMAGE) of the damage portion of the pbae songs.  To me it seems like that would be a simple change allowing you to just change a few numbers in the code.  Have them all be 1 dmg per tick as base values, even with a maxxed mod of 4.2 that bard would only be doing 4.2 a tick with that particular song.  Add in how many ever mobs you want and it's still not going to be worth it given kill times and risk/reward.  I'm no programmer but that seems like it would be an easy fix.<br><br>Someone else mentioned it in this thread about what you guys seem to prioritize.  It's sad.  I've recently cancelled my account due to ALOT of odd decisions you've made with the direction of this once fun game.  From listening too much, to ignoring long lasting bugs, to horrible customer service, the list really is so big that it'd take me awhile to remember some.  But through all of this I've actually been looking for something to recapture my interest to make me come back, then I read about this.  Wow.  Just when I thought you would start paying attention to bard issues(via top 10 lists) you go and do this.  If as you stated these things are so much work, why not get cracking on things we've TOLD you we've wanted addressed?  Change a line or two and get cracking on the real stuff, you're fighting an upward battle.<br><br>Get back to the vision.
																		
