												Really, just because one is able to kill 30 mobs at once does not mean its unbalanced. As others have said, other classes can get very comparable XP by killing smaller amounts of mobs, but faster. When it takes 10-20 minutes to pull a giant train, then another 20 minutes  to kill the group of mobs; the XP comes out to look really good because you get it all at once, but its just decent XP. Factor in pull time, plus kill time, plus repop time to calculate the XP over time and it really is not a massive number.<br><br>If anything, just make it take longer. Nerf the damage on the AE's if your moving or something. A long time ago dots used to do less damage if you were kiting. So the code exsists. Put it on the bard songs if you want. But really, totally nerfing AE kiting is absurd.
																		
